Feature Engineering¶

Based on our exploratory data analysis from before, since there is no inherent correlation between any of the initial Dataframe features, I have decided to drop features based on whether or not the rounded means and standard deviations are identical.

To achieve this, I will round the means and standard deviations, take the transpose of that matrix, drop identical/duplicate rows, and then retranspose it back.

The next thing we will do is to use the elbow plot method to determine the ideal number of clusters for our clustering.

In [15]:
def plot_inertia(km, X, n_cluster_range):
    inertias = []
    for i in n_cluster_range:
        km.set_params(n_clusters=i)
        km.fit(X)
        inertias.append(km.inertia_)
    plt.plot(n_cluster_range, inertias, marker='o')
    plt.title('Elbow method')
    plt.xlabel('Number of clusters')
    plt.ylabel('Inertia')
    plt.show()
    
plot_inertia(kmeans,removedDF, range(1,8))
